   377→## Caveats
   382→By default, `input-otp` handles password managers for you.
   383→The password manager badges should be automatically shifted to the right side.
   384→
   385→However, if you still want to block password managers, please disable the `pushPasswordManagerStrategy` and then manually block each PWM.
   386→
   387→```diff
   388→<OTPInput
   389→  // First, disable library's built-in strategy
   390→  // for shifting badges automatically
   391→- pushPasswordManagerStrategy="increase-width"
   392→+ pushPasswordManagerStrategy="none"
   393→  // Then, manually add specifics attributes
   394→  // your password manager docs
   395→  // Example: block LastPass
   396→+ data-lpignore="true" 
   397→  // Example: block 1Password
   398→+ data-1p-ignore="true"
   399→/>
   400→```
   401→</details>
   402→
   403→<details>
